'''Moritano Shrine''' (もりたのじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} ({{jalink|village shrine|Q134917284}}) located in {{jalink|Takada (Nagano City)|Q11672003|Takada}}, {{jalink|Nagano City|Q128849}}, {{jalink|Nagano Prefecture|Q127877}}. It is commonly known as '''Morita Shrine'''.

It is identified with the Morita Shrine listed as a {{jalink|Shikinaisha}}.

=== Overview ===
The shrine is located in a {{jalink|residential area}} in the eastern part of Nagano City, one street removed from the bustle of {{jalink|National Route 19|Q899326}}.

Although the date of foundation is unknown, it was formerly called '''Morita Hachimangū''' and served as the {{jalink|ujigami|Q1392097}} (tutelary deity) of the former {{jalink|Takada (Nagano City)|Q11672003|Kita-Takada Village}}<ref>[http://www.komakichiku.com/siseki/ Our Town’s Historic Sites and Cultural Properties] – Komaki District Residents’自治 Council</ref>. In {{jalink|1756|Q7632}} ({{jalink|Hōreki|Q1194397}} 8), it received {{jalink|heihaku|Q11481885}} under the name '''Morita Shrine''' from the {{jalink|Yoshida family|Q11413722}} of {{jalink|Shinto priests|Q60523}}. However, during the Shikinaisha naming dispute in {{jalink|1839|Q7616}} ({{jalink|Tenpō|Q1369045}} 10), the character “迺 (or 廼)” was added to its name.

The main hall was formerly the Year Deity Hall of {{jalink|Zenkō-ji|Q189640}}. When the Year Deity Hall was relocated from the Zenkō-ji precincts to {{jalink|Joyama Park (Nagano City)|Q11426101|Joyama}} as {{jalink|Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine (Nagano City, Hakoshimizu)|Q11387218|Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine}} (Minochi Taisha) following the {{jalink|separation of Shinto and Buddhism|Q1970535}}, only the building was transferred to this shrine<ref>[http://weekly-nagano.main.jp/2011/04/070.html No. 070 Moritano Shrine (Part 2) – The main hall transferred from Zenkō-ji] – Weekly Nagano</ref>.

Because it was relatively close to {{jalink|Tsuruga (Nagano City)#Higashi-Tsuruga Town|Q11676187|Tsuruga Shinchi}} (the former Nagano red-light district) and {{jalink|Gondō Town (Nagano City)|Q11542303|Gondō Town}}, many of the donors’ names carved on the {{jalink|tamagaiki|Q3078312}} fence belong to {{jalink|ryōtei|Q2178435}} restaurants and brothels<ref>[http://weekly-nagano.main.jp/2011/04/069.html No. 069 Moritano Shrine (Part 1) – Names of restaurants and pleasure quarters on the fence] – Weekly Nagano</ref>.

=== History ===
* {{jalink|1459|Q6524}} ({{jalink|Chōroku|Q1193524}} 3) – Relocated from a nearby site to its present location  
* {{jalink|1699|Q7710}} ({{jalink|Genroku|Q1325001}} 12) – Following a divine oracle, the sacred object was transferred from the Year Deity Hall of {{jalink|Zenkō-ji|Q189640}}  
* {{jalink|1756|Q7632}} ({{jalink|Hōreki|Q1194397}} 8) – Received {{jalink|heihaku|Q11481885}} from the {{jalink|Yoshida family|Q11413722}} under the name '''Morita Shrine'''  
* {{jalink|1839|Q7616}} ({{jalink|Tenpō|Q1369045}} 10) – Entered into a shrine name dispute (Shikinaisha dispute) with shrines of the same name in Furuma (present-day {{jalink|Shinanomachi (representative topic)||Shinanomachi}}) and {{jalink|Naganuma (Nagano City)|Q17226618|Naganuma}} (now part of {{jalink|Nagano City|Q128849}}); as the priest of this shrine was still young at the time, the result was a renaming to '''Moritano Shrine'''  
* {{jalink|1879|Q7783}} ({{jalink|Meiji|Q3125096}} 12) – The former Year Deity Hall of Zenkō-ji, which had been relocated in the same year to {{jalink|Joyama Park (Nagano City)|Q11426101|Joyama}} as {{jalink|Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine (Nagano City, Hakoshimizu)|Q11387218|Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine}} (Minochi Taisha), was transferred and rebuilt as this shrine’s main hall  
* {{jalink|1967|Q2648}} ({{jalink|Shōwa|Q327567}} 42) – The main hall was designated a {{jalink|Nagano City|Q128849}} {{jalink|designated cultural property}}

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{jalink|Emperor Ōjin|Q317997|Hondawake no Mikoto}} (principal deity)
* Kotoshironushi
* Ōusu no Mikoto
* Kuebiko no Mikoto
* Takeminakata no Mikoto
* Susanoo no Mikoto

=== Precincts ===
* Main hall – {{jalink|Nagano City|Q128849}} {{jalink|designated cultural property}}<ref>[http://bunkazai-nagano.jp/modules/dbsearch/page1049.html Moritano Shrine Main Hall] – Nagano City Cultural Properties Database</ref>. Former main hall of the Zenkō-ji Year Deity Hall  
* Worship hall  
* Norito hall  
* Auxiliary shrines  
