'''Moritano Shrine''' (もりたのじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} ({{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284}}) located in {{ill|lt=Takada (Nagano City)|Q11672003|WD=Q11672003|lt=Takada}}, {{ill|lt=Nagano City|Q128849|WD=Q128849}}, {{ill|lt=Nagano Prefecture|Q127877|WD=Q127877}}. It is commonly known as '''Morita Shrine'''.

It is identified with the Morita Shrine listed as a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=UNKNOWN|WD=Q134917286}}.

=== Overview ===
The shrine is located in a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=residential area|1=UNKNOWN}} in the eastern part of Nagano City, one street removed from the bustle of {{ill|lt=National Route 19|Q899326|WD=Q899326}}.

Although the date of foundation is unknown, it was formerly called '''Morita Hachimangū''' and served as the {{ill|lt=ujigami|Q1392097|WD=Q1392097}} (tutelary deity) of the former {{ill|lt=Takada (Nagano City)|Q11672003|WD=Q11672003|lt=Kita-Takada Village}}<ref>[http://www.komakichiku.com/siseki/ Our Town’s Historic Sites and Cultural Properties] – Komaki District Residents’自治 Council</ref>. In {{ill|lt=1756|Q7632|WD=Q7632}} ({{ill|lt=Hōreki|Q1194397|WD=Q1194397}} 8), it received {{ill|lt=heihaku|Q11481885|WD=Q11481885}} under the name '''Morita Shrine''' from the {{ill|lt=Yoshida family|Q11413722|WD=Q11413722}} of {{ill|lt=Shinto priests|Q60523|WD=Q60523}}. However, during the Shikinaisha naming dispute in {{ill|lt=1839|Q7616|WD=Q7616}} ({{ill|lt=Tenpō|Q1369045|WD=Q1369045}} 10), the character “迺 (or 廼)” was added to its name.

The main hall was formerly the Year Deity Hall of {{ill|lt=Zenkō-ji|Q189640|WD=Q189640}}. When the Year Deity Hall was relocated from the Zenkō-ji precincts to {{ill|lt=Joyama Park (Nagano City)|Q11426101|WD=Q11426101|lt=Joyama}} as {{ill|WD=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine (Nagano City, Hakoshimizu)|Q11387218|WD=Q11387218|WD=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine}} (Minochi Taisha) following the {{ill|lt=separation of Shinto and Buddhism|Q1970535|WD=Q1970535}}, only the building was transferred to this shrine<ref>[http://weekly-nagano.main.jp/2011/04/070.html No. 070 Moritano Shrine (Part 2) – The main hall transferred from Zenkō-ji] – Weekly Nagano</ref>.

Because it was relatively close to {{ill|lt=Tsuruga (Nagano City)#Higashi-Tsuruga Town|Q11676187|WD=Q11676187|lt=Tsuruga Shinchi}} (the former Nagano red-light district) and {{ill|lt=Gondō Town (Nagano City)|Q11542303|WD=Q11542303|lt=Gondō Town}}, many of the donors’ names carved on the {{ill|lt=tamagaiki|Q3078312|WD=Q3078312}} fence belong to {{ill|lt=ryōtei|Q2178435|WD=Q2178435}} restaurants and brothels<ref>[http://weekly-nagano.main.jp/2011/04/069.html No. 069 Moritano Shrine (Part 1) – Names of restaurants and pleasure quarters on the fence] – Weekly Nagano</ref>.

=== History ===
* {{ill|lt=1459|Q6524|WD=Q6524}} ({{ill|lt=Chōroku|Q1193524|WD=Q1193524}} 3) – Relocated from a nearby site to its present location  
* {{ill|lt=1699|Q7710|WD=Q7710}} ({{ill|lt=Genroku|Q1325001|WD=Q1325001}} 12) – Following a divine oracle, the sacred object was transferred from the Year Deity Hall of {{ill|lt=Zenkō-ji|Q189640|WD=Q189640}}  
* {{ill|lt=1756|Q7632|WD=Q7632}} ({{ill|lt=Hōreki|Q1194397|WD=Q1194397}} 8) – Received {{ill|lt=heihaku|Q11481885|WD=Q11481885}} from the {{ill|lt=Yoshida family|Q11413722|WD=Q11413722}} under the name '''Morita Shrine'''  
* {{ill|lt=1839|Q7616|WD=Q7616}} ({{ill|lt=Tenpō|Q1369045|WD=Q1369045}} 10) – Entered into a shrine name dispute (Shikinaisha dispute) with shrines of the same name in Furuma (present-day {{ill|lt=Shinanomachi (representative topic)|UNKNOWN|lt=Shinanomachi}}) and {{ill|lt=Naganuma (Nagano City)|Q17226618|WD=Q17226618|lt=Naganuma}} (now part of {{ill|lt=Nagano City|Q128849|WD=Q128849}}); as the priest of this shrine was still young at the time, the result was a renaming to '''Moritano Shrine'''  
* {{ill|lt=1879|Q7783|WD=Q7783}} ({{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096}} 12) – The former Year Deity Hall of Zenkō-ji, which had been relocated in the same year to {{ill|lt=Joyama Park (Nagano City)|Q11426101|WD=Q11426101|lt=Joyama}} as {{ill|WD=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine (Nagano City, Hakoshimizu)|Q11387218|WD=Q11387218|WD=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine}} (Minochi Taisha), was transferred and rebuilt as this shrine’s main hall  
* {{ill|lt=1967|Q2648|WD=Q2648}} ({{ill|lt=Shōwa|Q327567|WD=Q327567}} 42) – The main hall was designated a {{ill|lt=Nagano City|Q128849|WD=Q128849}} {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=designated cultural property|1=UNKNOWN}}

