'''Moritano Shrine''' (もりたのじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} ({{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}) located in {{ill|lt=Takada (Nagano City)|Q11672003|qid=Q11672003|lt=Takada|1=Takada}}, {{ill|lt=Nagano City|Q128849|qid=Q128849|1=Nagano (city)}}, {{ill|lt=Nagano Prefecture|Q127877|qid=Q127877|1=Nagano Prefecture}}. It is commonly known as '''Morita Shrine'''.

It is identified with the Morita Shrine listed as a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}}.

=== Overview ===
The shrine is located in a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=residential area|1=UNKNOWN}} in the eastern part of Nagano City, one street removed from the bustle of {{ill|lt=National Route 19|Q899326|qid=Q899326|1=Japan National Route 19}}.

Although the date of foundation is unknown, it was formerly called '''Morita Hachimangū''' and served as the {{ill|lt=ujigami|Q1392097|qid=Q1392097|1=Ubusunagami}} (tutelary deity) of the former {{ill|lt=Takada (Nagano City)|Q11672003|qid=Q11672003|lt=Kita-Takada Village|1=Kita-Takada Village}}<ref>[http://www.komakichiku.com/siseki/ Our Town’s Historic Sites and Cultural Properties] – Komaki District Residents’自治 Council</ref>. In {{ill|lt=1756|Q7632|qid=Q7632|1=1756}} ({{ill|lt=Hōreki|Q1194397|qid=Q1194397|1=Hōreki}} 8), it received {{ill|lt=heihaku|Q11481885|qid=Q11481885|1=Hanpei}} under the name '''Morita Shrine''' from the {{ill|lt=Yoshida family|Q11413722|qid=Q11413722|1=Yoshida family}} of {{ill|lt=Shinto priests|Q60523|qid=Q60523|1=Kannushi}}. However, during the Shikinaisha naming dispute in {{ill|lt=1839|Q7616|qid=Q7616|1=1839}} ({{ill|lt=Tenpō|Q1369045|qid=Q1369045|1=Tenpō}} 10), the character “迺 (or 廼)” was added to its name.

The main hall was formerly the Year Deity Hall of {{ill|lt=Zenkō-ji|Q189640|qid=Q189640|1=Zenkō-ji}}. When the Year Deity Hall was relocated from the Zenkō-ji precincts to {{ill|lt=Joyama Park (Nagano City)|Q11426101|qid=Q11426101|lt=Joyama|1=Jōyama Park}} as {{ill|qid=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine (Nagano City, Hakoshimizu)|Q11387218|qid=Q11387218|qid=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine|1=Takeminakata}} (Minochi Taisha) following the {{ill|lt=separation of Shinto and Buddhism|Q1970535|qid=Q1970535|1=Shinbutsu bunri}}, only the building was transferred to this shrine<ref>[http://weekly-nagano.main.jp/2011/04/070.html No. 070 Moritano Shrine (Part 2) – The main hall transferred from Zenkō-ji] – Weekly Nagano</ref>.

Because it was relatively close to {{ill|lt=Tsuruga (Nagano City)#Higashi-Tsuruga Town|Q11676187|qid=Q11676187|lt=Tsuruga Shinchi|1=Tsuruga}} (the former Nagano red-light district) and {{ill|lt=Gondō Town (Nagano City)|Q11542303|qid=Q11542303|lt=Gondō Town|1=Gondōchō}}, many of the donors’ names carved on the {{ill|lt=tamagaiki|Q3078312|qid=Q3078312|1=Sacred fences}} fence belong to {{ill|lt=ryōtei|Q2178435|qid=Q2178435|1=Ryōtei}} restaurants and brothels<ref>[http://weekly-nagano.main.jp/2011/04/069.html No. 069 Moritano Shrine (Part 1) – Names of restaurants and pleasure quarters on the fence] – Weekly Nagano</ref>.

=== History ===
* {{ill|lt=1459|Q6524|qid=Q6524|1=1459}} ({{ill|lt=Chōroku|Q1193524|qid=Q1193524|1=Chōroku}} 3) – Relocated from a nearby site to its present location  
* {{ill|lt=1699|Q7710|qid=Q7710|1=1699}} ({{ill|lt=Genroku|Q1325001|qid=Q1325001|1=Genroku}} 12) – Following a divine oracle, the sacred object was transferred from the Year Deity Hall of {{ill|lt=Zenkō-ji|Q189640|qid=Q189640|1=Zenkō-ji}}  
* {{ill|lt=1756|Q7632|qid=Q7632|1=1756}} ({{ill|lt=Hōreki|Q1194397|qid=Q1194397|1=Hōreki}} 8) – Received {{ill|lt=heihaku|Q11481885|qid=Q11481885|1=Hanpei}} from the {{ill|lt=Yoshida family|Q11413722|qid=Q11413722|1=Yoshida family}} under the name '''Morita Shrine'''  
* {{ill|lt=1839|Q7616|qid=Q7616|1=1839}} ({{ill|lt=Tenpō|Q1369045|qid=Q1369045|1=Tenpō}} 10) – Entered into a shrine name dispute (Shikinaisha dispute) with shrines of the same name in Furuma (present-day {{ill|lt=Shinanomachi (representative topic)|UNKNOWN|lt=Shinanomachi}}) and {{ill|lt=Naganuma (Nagano City)|Q17226618|qid=Q17226618|lt=Naganuma|1=Naganuma}} (now part of {{ill|lt=Nagano City|Q128849|qid=Q128849|1=Nagano (city)}}); as the priest of this shrine was still young at the time, the result was a renaming to '''Moritano Shrine'''  
* {{ill|lt=1879|Q7783|qid=Q7783|1=1879}} ({{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|qid=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 12) – The former Year Deity Hall of Zenkō-ji, which had been relocated in the same year to {{ill|lt=Joyama Park (Nagano City)|Q11426101|qid=Q11426101|lt=Joyama|1=Jōyama Park}} as {{ill|qid=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine (Nagano City, Hakoshimizu)|Q11387218|qid=Q11387218|qid=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata Tomino Mikoto Hikokamiwake Shrine|1=Takeminakata}} (Minochi Taisha), was transferred and rebuilt as this shrine’s main hall  
* {{ill|lt=1967|Q2648|qid=Q2648|1=1967}} ({{ill|lt=Shōwa|Q327567|qid=Q327567|1=Shōwa era}} 42) – The main hall was designated a {{ill|lt=Nagano City|Q128849|qid=Q128849|1=Nagano (city)}} {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=designated cultural property|1=UNKNOWN}}

